         <c id="ref17" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Microfilm HM 135, 1937-1943</unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_7bca4be7e2178e043d7fd4ba9154c78b">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>HM Film 135 records three scrapbooks kept by Mortison. The first two contain the printed copies of his cartoons, clipped from the Waterbury newspapers, with some photographs and other clippings; the third contains clippings about the trial. A few pages contain Mortison's later annotations, so that the inclusive dates for the film are 1937-1943.</p>
            </scopecontent>
